  "summary": "Critical: keylime security update",
  "details": "Keylime is a TPM based highly scalable remote boot attestation and runtime integrity measurement solution.  \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * keylime: Keylime: Authentication bypass allows unauthorized administrative operations due to missing client-side TLS authentication (CVE-2026-1709)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
